**Custom tab not cleared on removal**

If an application previously had `settingsCustomTabFrontComponentUniversalIdentifier` set in its manifest and a subsequent manifest update removes it, the `settingsCustomTabFrontComponentId` stays `null` here, so `isDefined(null)` returns `false`, and the field is never included in the update call. This means the old `settingsCustomTabFrontComponentId` value persists in the database and the custom tab remains visible even though the app no longer defines one.

Unlike `defaultRoleUniversalIdentifier` (which is required in `ApplicationManifest` and thus always present), `settingsCustomTabFrontComponentUniversalIdentifier` is optional and can be removed. Consider explicitly setting `settingsCustomTabFrontComponentId: null` in the update when the manifest no longer specifies it:

```suggestion
    let settingsCustomTabFrontComponentId: string | null = null;

    const settingsCustomTabUniversalIdentifier =
      manifest.application.settingsCustomTabFrontComponentUniversalIdentifier;

    if (isDefined(settingsCustomTabUniversalIdentifier)) {
      const flatFrontComponent = findFlatEntityByUniversalIdentifier({
        flatEntityMaps: refreshedFlatFrontComponentMaps,
        universalIdentifier: settingsCustomTabUniversalIdentifier,
      });

      if (!isDefined(flatFrontComponent)) {
        throw new ApplicationException(
          `Failed to resolve front component for settingsCustomTabFrontComponentUniversalIdentifier ${settingsCustomTabUniversalIdentifier}`,
          ApplicationExceptionCode.ENTITY_NOT_FOUND,
        );
      }

      settingsCustomTabFrontComponentId = flatFrontComponent.id;
    }

    if (
      isDefined(defaultRoleId) ||
      isDefined(settingsCustomTabFrontComponentId) ||
      !isDefined(settingsCustomTabUniversalIdentifier)
    ) {
      await this.applicationService.update(ownerFlatApplication.id, {
        ...(isDefined(defaultRoleId) ? { defaultRoleId } : {}),
        ...(!isDefined(settingsCustomTabUniversalIdentifier)
          ? { settingsCustomTabFrontComponentId: null }
          : isDefined(settingsCustomTabFrontComponentId)
            ? { settingsCustomTabFrontComponentId }
            : {}),
      });
    }
```

**`AsyncExecutionResult` field name mismatch with actual API**

The `AsyncExecutionResult` interface declares `taskId: string`, but `sim.service.ts` line 292 documents the actual API response shape as `{ success, async, jobId, executionId, message, statusUrl }` — the field is `jobId`, not `taskId`. This discrepancy causes the status logic in `triggerEventWorkflow` (line 545) to silently fail since `asyncResult.taskId` will always be `undefined` when the API returns `jobId`.

The workaround on line 293 (`(result as any).jobId || asyncResult.taskId`) indicates the developer is aware of the mismatch, but leaving the type wrong makes it easy to reintroduce the bug. The type should be corrected to match the actual API contract:

```suggestion
	export interface AsyncExecutionResult {
		success: boolean;
		jobId: string;
		status: 'queued';
		createdAt: string;
		links: { status: string };
	}
```

