Missing final TextDecoder flush — incomplete multi-byte UTF-8 sequences will be silently dropped.

`decoder.decode(value, { stream: true })` inside the loop deliberately holds back incomplete code-points to handle split UTF-8 boundaries. After the loop exits, any partial bytes buffered inside the decoder are never emitted to `chunks`, which means multi-byte characters (Chinese, Japanese, emoji) at chunk boundaries will be silently truncated or lost.

Add a final flush after the loop to emit any remaining buffered bytes:

```suggestion
    try {
      while (true) {
        const { done, value } = await reader.read()
        if (done) break
        chunks.push(decoder.decode(value, { stream: true }))
      }
      // Flush any remaining bytes buffered by the streaming decoder
      const tail = decoder.decode()
      if (tail) chunks.push(tail)
    } catch (error) {
      logger.error('Error reading executor stream for block', { blockId, error })
    } finally {
      try {
        await reader.cancel().catch(() => {})
      } catch {}
    }
```

**`initialMessage` prop changes are not synced to internal state — breaks URL-prefilled prompts in NRFPage**

The `useEffect` that kept the internal `message` state in sync with prop changes to `initialMessage` has been removed. Because `useState(initialMessage)` only uses the initial value on mount, subsequent changes to the prop are ignored.

This breaks the NRFPage flow where the component mounts with `initialMessage=""`, then after mount a `useEffect` reads `window.location.search` and updates its `message` state:
1. NRFPage mounts AppInputBar with `initialMessage=""` 
2. AppInputBar mounts and sets internal `message=""` via `useState`
3. NRFPage's `useEffect` (lines 143–151 of NRFPage.tsx) fires and calls `setMessage(userPrompt)` 
4. NRFPage re-renders with `initialMessage={userPrompt}` 
5. **But AppInputBar ignores it** — no effect to sync the new prop value to internal state

The sync effect must be restored:

```suggestion
const [message, setMessage] = useState(initialMessage);
const textAreaRef = useRef<HTMLTextAreaElement>(null);
const textAreaWrapperRef = useRef<HTMLDivElement>(null);
const filesWrapperRef = useRef<HTMLDivElement>(null);
const filesContentRef = useRef<HTMLDivElement>(null);
const containerRef = useRef<HTMLDivElement>(null);
const { user } = useUser();
const { isClassifying, classification } = useQueryController();

// Expose reset and focus methods to parent via ref
React.useImperativeHandle(ref, () => ({
  reset: () => {
    setMessage("");
  },
  focus: () => {
    textAreaRef.current?.focus();
  },
}));

// Sync prop changes to internal state
useEffect(() => {
  if (initialMessage) {
    setMessage(initialMessage);
  }
}, [initialMessage]);
```

