The same class of bug can still occur in `analyzeOutputRoutingTable` when the *first* node in a routing-table branch (`i == 0`) is void. In that situation `prevOutputHandle` stays as the zero value `ir.Handle{}`. When `i == 1` is processed, the edge `Source: prevOutputHandle` will carry an empty handle (`Node: "", Param: ""`), which — just like the original bug — will cause `state.Node()` to look up a non-existent entry at runtime and dereference nil.

